company.description:
The Insurance Commission of Western Australia is a statutory corporation, or Government Trading Enterprise, owned by the State Government of Western Australia. The Insurance Commission is primarily responsible for:

•	administering, underwriting and managing WA’s motor injury insurance;
•	managing RiskCover, the self-insurance arrangements on behalf of the WA Government;
•	investing and managing the funds to provide assets to meet insurance liabilities; and
•	advising the WA Government about insurance matters.
